        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2538009668" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8387967714819276172">The Mysterious Affair at Styles is Agatha Christies first published novel and the introduction of Poirot to the world. While it suffers from the fact that Poirot is not the calm and methodical detective he would later become it soars in the plotting and intricacy of the mystery. What would seem to be a straightforward murder mystery becomes a tangled web of clues - a Christie trait that she establishes from the very beginning. Moreover, just as she would later make her trademark, all the clues a</span>
  <span id="freeText8387967714819276172" style="display:none">The Mysterious Affair at Styles is Agatha Christies first published novel and the introduction of Poirot to the world. While it suffers from the fact that Poirot is not the calm and methodical detective he would later become it soars in the plotting and intricacy of the mystery. What would seem to be a straightforward murder mystery becomes a tangled web of clues - a Christie trait that she establishes from the very beginning. Moreover, just as she would later make her trademark, all the clues are there in front of the reader. It takes the mind of Poirot to put them together. This is a "MUST READ!"</span>
  <a data-text-id="8387967714819276172" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

